ior first (usually reckoned by date of consecration); use | suffragan = for one -->\n| auxiliary_bishops = <!-- List most senior first (usually reckoned by date of consecration) -->\n| apostolic_admin   = \n| vicar_general     = \n| episcopal_vicar   =\n| judicial_vicar    =\n| dean              = \n| archdeacons       = <!-- List most senior first (usually reckoned by date of first collation); use | archdeacon = for one-->\n| emeritus_bishops  = <!-- List most senior first (usually reckoned by date of consecration) -->\n<!---- Map ---->\n| map               = \n| map_size          = \n| map_alt           = \n| map_caption       = \n<!---- Website ---->\n| website           = [https://kirken.no/nb-NO/bispedommer/Hamar/ Website of the Diocese] \n| footnotes         = \n}}\nThe '''Diocese of Hamar'''  (Norwegian: ''Hamar Bisped\u00f8mme'') is one of the dioceses that make up the [[Church of Norway]].  \nThe diocese of Hamar covers the churches of [[Oppland]] and [[Hedmark]]. There are 164 parishes in the diocese. [[Hamar Cathedral]] (''Hamar domkirke'') in the  city of  [[Hamar]] is the seat of the Diocese of Hamar. \n<ref>{{cite web|url =    https://snl.no/Hamar_bisped%C3%B8mme|title= Hamar bisped\u00f8mme|publisher =    Store norske leksikon\n|author=  Hallgeir Elstad|accessdate=September 1, 2018}}</ref>\n<ref>{{cite web|url = https://snl.no/Hamar_domkirke._-_Kirke_i_Hamar_kommune|title= Hamar domkirke. \u2013 Kirke i Hamar kommune|publisher =    Store norske leksikon\n|author=  Nina Aldin Thune|accessdate=September 1, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==History==\nThe Roman Catholic Diocese of Hamar was formed in 1152 out of the Diocese of Oslo. At the time of the [[Protestant Reformation]] in 1536, the Archbishop and the bishops were removed and the Diocese of Hamar once again came  under the [[Diocese of Oslo]]. [[Mogens Lauritsson]] was the last Roman Catholic bishop of the [[Ancient Diocese of Hamar]]. After  separation from the Diocese of Oslo, the Lutheran Diocese of Hamar was established in 1864. [[Halvor Olsen Folkestad]] was the first  bishop of the current Diocese of Hamar. [[Hamar Cathedral]] was consecrated for services on 15 December 1866 and established as the seat of the present Diocese of Hamar.\n<ref>{{cite web|url =    https://lokalhistoriewiki.no/index.php/Hamar_bisped%C3%B8mmeindex.php/Hamar_bisped%C3%B8mme|title= Hamar bisped\u00f8mme\n|publisher =   lokalhistoriewiki.no|accessdate=September 1, 2018}}</ref>\n<ref>{{cite web|url =   https://kirken.no/nb-NO/bispedommer/Hamar/om-oss/historien/  |title= Hamar bisped\u00f8mme 1536-1567|publisher =  Hamar Biskop Og Bisped\u00f8mmer\u00e5d\n|accessdate=September 1, 2018}}</ref>\n<ref>{{cite web|url =https://snl.no/Halvor_Olsen_Folkestad |title= Halvor Olsen Folkestad|publisher =    Store norske leksikon|author=  Hallgeir Elstad\n|accessdate=September 1, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Structure==\nThe Diocese of Hamar is divided into ten [[deanery|deaneries]] ({{lang-no|Prosti}}) spread out over [[Innlandet]] and [[Viken (county)|Viken]] counties.  Each deanery corresponds a geographical area, usually one or more municipalities in the diocese.  Each municipality is further divided into one or more [[parish]]es which each contain one or more congregations.  \n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Deanery (''Prosti'') !! Municipalities !! County\n|-\n|[[:no:Hamar domprosti|Hamar domprosti]]||[[Hamar]], [[L\u00f8ten]], [[Stange]]||rowspan=\"9\"|[[Innlandet]]\n|-\n|[[:no:Ringsaker prosti|Ringsaker prosti]]||[[Ringsaker]]\n|-\n|[[:no:Sol\u00f8r, Vinger og Odal prosti|Sol\u00f8r,Vinger og Odal prosti]]||[[Kongsvinger]], [[Eidskog]], [[S\u00f8r-Odal]], [[Nord-Odal]], [[Grue, Norway|Grue]], [[\u00c5snes]], [[V\u00e5ler, Norway|V\u00e5ler]]\n|-\n|[[:no:S\u00f8r-\u00d8sterdal prosti|S\u00f8r-\u00d8sterdal prosti]]||[[\u00c5mot]], [[Elverum]], [[Trysil]], [[Engerdal]], [[Stor-Elvdal]]\n|-\n|[[:no:Nord-\u00d8sterdal prosti|Nord-\u00d8sterdal prosti]]||[[Tynset]], [[Alvdal]], [[Folldal]], [[Rendalen]], [[Tolga, Norway|Tolga]], [[Os, Norway|Os]]\n|-\n|[[:no:Nord-Gudbrandsdal prosti|Nord-Gudbrandsdal prosti]]||[[Dovre]], [[Lesja]], [[Lom, Norway|Lom]], [[Nord-Fron]], [[Sel]], [[Skj\u00e5k]], [[V\u00e5g\u00e5]]\n|-\n|[[:no:S\u00f8r-Gudbrandsdal prosti|S\u00f8r-Gudbrandsdal prosti]]||[[Gausdal]], [[Lillehammer]], [[Ringebu]], [[S\u00f8r-Fron]], [[\u00d8yer]]\n|-\n|[[:nn:Toten prosti|Toten prosti]]||[[Gj\u00f8vik]], [[\u00d8stre Toten]], [[Vestre Toten]]\n|-\n|[[:no:Hadeland og Land prosti|Hadeland og Land prosti]]||[[Gran, Norway|Gran]], [[S\u00f8ndre Land]], [[Nordre Land]]\n|-\n|[[:no:Hadeland og Land prosti|Hadeland og Land prosti]]||[[Jevnaker]], [[Lunner]]||[[Viken (county)|Viken]]\n|-\n|[[:no:Valdres prosti|Valdres prosti]]||[[S\u00f8r-Aurdal]], [[Nord-Aurdal]], [[Etnedal]], [[\u00d8ystre Slidre]], [[Vestre Slidre]], [[Vang, Innlandet|Vang]]||[[Innlandet]]\n|-\n|}\n\n==List of bishops==\nIn reverse chronolocial order, the following bishops have led the diocese:\n\n*2006\u2013present : [[Solveig Fiske]]<ref>{{cite web|url = https://snl.no/Solveig_Fiske |title= Solveig Fiske|publisher =    Store norske leksikon\n|author=  Hallgeir Elstad|accessdate=September 1, 2018}}</ref>\n*1993&ndash;2006 : [[Rosemarie K\u00f6hn]]\n*1974&ndash;1993 : [[Georg Hille]]\n*1964&ndash;1974 : [[Alexander Johnson (Norwegian bishop)|Alexander Johnson]]\n*1947&ndash;1964 : [[Kristian Vilhelm Koren Schjelderup, Jr.|Kristian Schjelderup]]\n*1945&ndash;1947 : [[Henrik Hille]]\n*1943&ndash;1945 : [[Sigurd Haga]] (appointed by [[Nasjonal Samling]])\n*1942&ndash;1943 : [[Georg Falck-Hansen]] (appointed by Nasjonal Samling)\n*1934&ndash;1942 : [[Henrik Hille]]\n*1922&ndash;1934 : [[Mikkel Bj\u00f8nness-Jacobsen]]\n*1918&ndash;1922 : [[Gustav Johan Fredrik Dietrichson]]\n*1917&ndash;1918 : [[Otto Jensen]]\n*1906&ndash;1917 : [[Christen Brun]]\n*1887&ndash;1906 : [[Arnoldus Hille]]\n*1864&ndash;1887 : [[Halvor Olsen Folkestad]]\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n==External links==\n*[http://www.norgeskirker.no/wiki/Kategori:Hamar_bisped%C3%B8mme Hamar bisped\u00f8mme] Norges Kirker\n{{Bishops of Norway}}\n\n[[Category:Organisations based in Hamar]]\n[[Category:Church of Norway dioceses|Hamar]]\n[[Category:Religious organizations established in 1864]]\n[[Category:1864 establishments in Norway]]\n", "name_user": "Redriv", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eStructure:rearranged rows", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diocese_of_Hamar"}
{"title_page": "Lakhahi", "text_new": "{{moresources|date=March 2020}}\n{{short description|Village in Uttar Pradesh, India}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=February 2020}}\n'''Lakhahi''' is a village and a large [[Gram panchayat]] in [[Dhaurehra]] tehsil [[Lakhimpur Kheri district]], Uttar Pradesh state, [[India]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mapsofindia.com/villages/uttar-pradesh/kheri/dhaurahara/lakhahi.html|title=Map of Lakhahi Village in Dhaurahara Tehsil, Kheri, Uttar Pradesh|website=Mapsofindia.com|url-status=live|access-date=5 October 2019}}</ref> It is a erstwhile Independent Princely State and a Zamindari Estate.  \n\nLakhahi was earlier famous for Ketki Flower.  \n\n<br />   \n\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                            = Lakhahi\n| subdivision_type                = Country\n| subdivision_name                = {{Flag|India}}\n| subdivision_type1               = State\n| subdivision_name1               = [[Uttar Pradesh]]\n| subdivision_type2               = District\n| subdivision_name2               = [[Lakhimpur Kheri district|Lakhimpur Kheri]]\n| governing_body                  = [[Gram panchayat]]\n| founder                         = Maharaja Shri Akhai Raj Singh Rathore{{cn|date=November 2019}}\n| registration_plate              = UP- 31\n| population_total                = 5510\n| settlement_type                 = Village\n| population_as_of                = 2011\n| government_type                 = [[Sarpanch]] (Pradhan)\n| coordinates                     = {{coord|28.16|N|80.97|E| display=inline,title}}\n| pushpin_map                     = India Uttar Pradesh#India#Asia\n| pushpin_map_caption             = Location in Uttar Pradesh, India\n| pushpin_label_position          = Right\n| official_name                   = \n| image_shield                    = PSX_20190910_220033_edited.jpg\n| translit_lang1                  = \n| website                         = \n| established_date                = c