 Memory and the Story of Benjamin Banneker's Grandmother|type=M.A.|location=[[Amherst, Massachusetts]]|publisher=[[University of Massachusetts Amherst]] |work=Masters Theses 1911-February 2014: Paper 210: ScholarWorks@UMass Amherst|oclc=314413559}}\n:*[http://scholarworks.umass.edu/theses/210/ Introduction and abstract.] Retrieved 2015-11-15. {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150929100518/http://scholarworks.umass.edu/theses/210/|date=September 29, 2015}}\n:*[http://scholarworks.umass.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=1215&context=theses Full text] Retrieved March 1, 2018.  {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151001211829/http://scholarworks.umass.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=1215&context=theses|date=October 1, 2015}}\n* {{cite journal|last=Phillips|first=P. Lee|year=1917|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=LSkkCeq5R1AC&pg=PA114#v=onepage&q&f=false|title=The Negro, Benjamin Banneker; Astronomer and Mathematician, Plea for Universal Peace (Read before the Society, April 18, 1916)|work=Records of the Columbia Historical Society|publisher=Columbia Historical Society, Washington, D.C.|volume=20|pages=114\u2013120|issn=0897-9049|lccn=18019397|oclc=1564221|accessdate=2009-04-15|via=[[Google Books]]}}\n*{{cite journal|last=Stewart|first=John|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=GgULOzNSafMC&pg=PA48#v=onepage&q&f=false|title=Early Maps and Surveyors of the City of Washington, D.C.|year=1899|journal=Records of the Columbia Historical Society|publisher=[[Historical Society of Washington, D.C.|Columbia Historical Society]]|location=Washington, D.C.|volume=2|pages=48\u201371|issn=0897-9049|oclc=40326234|accessdate=2011-08-15|via=[[Google Books]]}}\n* {{cite book|last=Tise|first=Larry E.|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170616001926/https://books.google.com/books?id=T1F1H2KUj80C&pg=PA213#v=onepage&q&f=false|title=Africans in the Land of Liberty: African-American Enlightenment|work=The American Counterrevolution: A Retreat from Liberty, 1783\u20131800